					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7220617#post-4351400</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-7220617/scp-4049#post-4351400</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Thu, 05 Sep 2019 03:35:57 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>5150wned</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5175695</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I read it all and it took me awhile for me to realize why it was that I wanted to -1 this in spite of my typical standard. There's nothing really wrong with it, even if it is rather simple, I don't downvote simple skips.</p> <p>The problem is twofold. The -2 can control electronic coms? It's mad that the Foundation has been killing it's pets? You've got some backstory to how this all works but it's too esoteric to understand, and not in a good way. Sometimes it is good to say &quot;shit be weird, cause anomaly, the end&quot;, but you have to stick to that instead of throwing in an ambiguous origin in order to say &quot;oh, it's like this cause of that&quot; without filling in the corners, which is what it feels like here.</p> <p>The other problem is that where you have untapped potential, you've taken (what seems to me) as the most basic route. The setting is the central northwest US, and you've got Greek letters and an eldritch horror that speaks English. It's pretty tame considering you could have gone along the lines of <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-1826">SCP-1826</a> and linked it to native folklore, or French trappers/hunters known to operate in that wilderness before the arrival of American loggers, miners, and farmers.</p> <p>-1</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
